Description: Lustre Introduction
Date: 3-31-2025
Author: Sean Krajewski


Luster is an open-source parallel distributed file system that is designed for HPC and large-scale data storage

Developed by Carnegie Mello University and is now actively maintained by OpenSFS (Open Scalable file systems, inc.)
Good for extensive storage capacity and high data throughput
used by most HPCs out there today


You have three parts to it
clients
Metadata service (MDS) MDT i.e. stores the meta data
Object Storage Servers - handles the actual data storage

So why use it?
Good for bandwith i.e. data transfer rates of +10Gps
Lustre uses the infiniband network